article.description: Greg Pryor scored 19 points, including four 3-pointers, and Chattanooga overtook Wofford in the second half for a 73-65 win Saturday night.
article.headline: Chattanooga slips past Wofford 73-65
article.story: SPARTANBURG, S.C. -- Greg Pryor scored 19 points, including four 3-pointers, and Chattanooga overtook Wofford in the second half for a 73-65 win Saturday night. Justin Tuoyo added 11 points and Casey Jones and Rodney Chatman had 10 apiece for Chattanooga, which shot 63 percent in the second half. Pryor was 6 of 9 from the field overall, collected eight rebounds and had three assists. Trailing by four at the break, Chattanooga (18-7, 9-4 Southern Conference) took the lead during a 17-2 run that included two 3-pointers from Nat Dixon and one from Tre' McLean to make it 67-60 with just over a minute to play. Wofford (13-14, 8-6) twice trimmed the gap back to four but Chattanooga hung on down the stretch to snap the Terriers' four-game win streak. Fletcher Magee led Wofford with 26 points and Ryan Sawvell added 16 to go with 11 rebounds.
